		li
			a(href="https://slack.design/accessibility-a-powerful-design-tool-22f5e6d46278") Accessibility, a powerful design tool

	h3 Animations
	ul
		li Learn to make <a href="https://alistapart.com/article/designing-safer-web-animation-for-motion-sensitivity/">animations for users with motion sensitivity. Then use <a href="https://alistapart.com/blog/post/more-resources-for-accessible-animations/">these resources</a> to put it into practice.

	h2 Business Implications
	p It's smart to make your website accessible. It's <a href="http://www.ilo.org/global/about-the-ilo/newsroom/features/WCMS_206049/lang--en/index.htm">good for society and business</a>. Learn to <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/business-case/">make a business case</a> for it. It will <a href="http://simplyaccessible.com/article/accessibility-according-to-my-mechanic/">expand the customer base</a>. Here are <a href="https://www.sitepoint.com/3-great-reasons-make-website-accessible/">3 specific ways accessibility benefits businesses</a>, and <a href="https://www.webdesignerdepot.com/2015/04/8-reasons-to-embrace-website-accessibility/">another 8 reasons</a>. Beyond the legal & economic reasons, remember that we're all disabled <a href="http://digitaldesignstandards.com/standard/accessibility/designing-accessibility-simply-good-business/">at least some of the time</a>, so we'll all need the functionality.

